es an explicit\n`--transcript-path`; discovery is documented as future work in\n[Capture Workflow](capture-workflow.md).\n\nUseful fields:\n\n| Field        | Claude source                                                     | If missing                               |\n| ------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------\n[TRUNCATED]\nscript list is the readable timeline; the hash set\nis the compact append index.\n\n\n`source-key` identifies the captured source file and uses the same\n`sha256-hex16(...)` format over the agent plus canonical transcript path bytes.\n\n## Transcript Records\n\nKeep one ordered `:transcript` list per durable GitButler session. Each list item\nis one redacted JSON transcript record with only per-record data:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n\t\"record_index\": 0,\n\t\"record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n\t\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-07T09:08:43.427Z\",\n\t\"event_kind\": \"response_item\",\n\t\"role\": \"assistant\",\n\t\"content_text\": \"redacted normalized text when easy to extract\",\n\t\"tool_name\": null,\n\t\"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSlim normalized fields support timeline browsing and handoff without reparsing\nevery provider-specific record:\n\n- `event_kind`: provider event type, with a nested event type when obvious\n- `role` and `content_text`: conversation body when extraction is obvious\n- `tool_name`: obvious tool activity\n- `source_record`: redacted provider record for provenance and future adapters\n\nOmit repeated session/source metadata from each transcript record. Also omit git\nbranch, provider session ids, message ids, parent ids, and turn ids from\ntop-level record fields.\n\nRecord hashes and dedupe use the original trimmed JSONL bytes, not the redacted\ntranscript record.\n\n## Deduplication\n\nUse stable record hashes:\n\n```text\nsha256(trimmed raw JSONL line bytes)\n```\n\nExpected access pattern:\n\n1. fetch or otherwise exchange GitMeta data for the repository\n2. read `gitbutler:agent-sessions` from the `project` target\n3. choose a session, either by recency, user selection, or a future explicit\n   relationship\n4. read `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:transcript`\n5. reconstruct useful context from `role`, `content_text`, `tool_name`,\n   `event_kind`, and redacted `source_record`\n\nThat means the transcript list must be readable without knowing the original\nmachine's file paths, working-directory state, branch state, or raw provider\nsession id.\n\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T10:57:38.486Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}